 What aspects are managed by Maven?
 build
 documentation
 reporting
 SCMs
 releases
 distribution
 ....................................................................................................
 
What are the advantages of Maven?
No need to add jar file in each project
Creates right directory structure
Builds and deploys the project
................................................................................................................................

What is the command to check the maven version?
mvn -version
.....................................................................................................................................

What does the build tool?
1)Generates source code (if the auto-generated code is used)
2)Generates documentation from source code
3)Compiles source code
4)Packages compiled code into a JAR or ZIP file
5)Installs the packaged code in the local repository, server repository, or central repository.
......................................................................................................................................

 What is  Maven?

It is a framework.
It is mainly a project management tool.
There is alife cycle.
Maven has a convention to place source code, compiled code etc.
Maven is declarative.
The Maven plugins are reusable.
