..................................................................................................................................

 What is a MOJO?
A MOJO stands for Maven plain Old Java Object.
.....................................................................................................................................

What is a repository?
repository is directory where jar and POM files stored.
there are 3 type
local repository:Maven local repository is created by maven in your local system when you run any maven command.

central:Maven community creates maven central repository on the web. 

remote:aven remote repository is located on the web by different vendors. So you need to define the dependency in pom.xml file manually.
 It is important because most of the libraries are missing from the central repository.
 ...................................................................................................................................
 
 What is POM?
POM stands for Project Object Model. The pom.xml file contains information of project and
 project configuration.
